DSTV Premiership newbies Richards Bay FC have announced their new-signing ahead of the 2022-23 season. The club was promoted to the Premiership after being crowned GladAfrica Championship champions last season. As they prepare for life in the elite league, they have roped in some experienced players whom they belive will help them compete on their first season. The Natal Rich BoyzÂ also unveiled former AmaZulu assistant coach Vasili Manousakis who joins them on technical advisor capacity where he will work with head coach Pitso Dladla and assistant coach Ronnie Gabriel. The club unveiled 10 new players, Yanela Mbuthuma, Michael Gumede, Matome Mabeba, Thulani Gumede, Sibusiso Mthethwa, Sanele Barns, Abel Mabaso, Dlamini Siyanda, Nkanysio Zungu and Ndiviwe Mdabuka. Wayward Zungu joins the club from Orlando Pirates on a season loan deal, while Mabaso who is also from Pirates is joining the club on a permanent move. @RichardsBayFC_ new signings. @dailysunsa @SunSportSA pic.twitter.com/1KbsrW7gm5 